d of stone fence by Gid\nWeathersby, prop. of our general store.\nseveral bales of breakfast food, by Hen\nTwo new shelves, to make room for\nHoskins,\n\nNew door put or his cellar by Cy\nSkinner.\nSeveral chicken coops by Widow\nand 3 of P.\n\u2018by Ame Hillyer, our talented legal light\nAn addishion built onto his kitchen\nBradbury.\nFront palings repaired by Deacon\nbuilder.\n\u2018barn by Lem Brown, our carpenter and\nNew grain bin in Dog Livermore's\nbyl Hez Andrews.\n\nHen house, 6 x 9, if boards hold out,\ning list, viz, towit:\ngivin in this conneckshion the follow\nbe built, and we take grate pleasure in\npose of findin out jest whot is going to\nthe interests of the Bugle for the pur\na house to house canvas tother day in\ncompleshion without delay. We made\nwill be pushed rapidly forward tords\nand now the weather is gettin better\ning in our midst wich has been laid out\nthink else, is the large amount of build\nof this boom, perhaps more than enny\nOne thing that indicates the growth\nis coming true.\nit had time enuf. \"Our prophetic words\nCo. seat) would grow and prosper if\n(being as it is only 15 miles from the\nness to civilisashion, as you might :ay\nto its natural advantages and its near\nollus sed however that Bingville, owing\nare much pleased to note it. We have\nveer of all yeers, but nevertheless we\ntribute this boom te, espeshially this\ncountry. We don't know whet to at\nwith other populous centers thruout the\nhelp this town take her place erlong\nwill do more than else to\nwill be far reaching in its effeck and\nthat this is a presidential year, wich\nboom this spring, in spite of the fackt\ndicate be on the\nThe Leading Paper of the County!\nTHE. BINGVILLE BUGLE!\nBright\u2014Breezy\u2014Bellicose\u2014~Bustiing\nBow doth the busy little des\n\nTr EL\nt ney a\nday\nIa opening Sour,\nThe advertising medium in the\ncomtry. If you believe in advertising, come\nt\nand see us. For further information call on\nor address the editor.\n\n\nTHE WASHINGTON HERALD, SUNDAY, APRIL 5 1803.\n\nAn Apology\nIt Is with deep regret we haft to send\nout this week's Bugle with our editorial\nsomewhot mixed up and natchurally our\narmy of readers will look for a explana\nshion somers in the paper and so here it\nis:\n\nOMKE CRICK\nLast Friday morning Bill Hepburn come\ninto our offise and sed he had to make a\nspesghial trip to the Co. seat to get some\nbolts and supplies and ast us to accom\npany him. Wa accepted the invite with\ngrate cheer, being as we haye been stickin\npurty close to werk this winter and went\nwith Bill. At the Co. seat we met sev.\neral old friends at five or six different\nplaces and after dinner Rill hitched up\nand we started for Bingville. On the\nway Bill he lickered up and before we\nreached Teck's Hill he managed to throw\nus out of the buggy twice while he sot\nIn the waggon and laffed fit to bust.\nWhen we finally reached Bingville at 3\no'clock Bill went to his shop while we\nunlacked our offise and went to work. We\nwas that tired from riding in Bill's rieck\nety old waggen that we could hardly walk\nand stept on the offise cat with ene foot\nand into the ash pan with the ather be\nfore we got our coat off. Then we tried\nto take our boots off without using our\nboot jack and we lest our balunce and\ntipped the paste pot all over us. By that\ntime our head begin te ache =o bad we\ncould scalrsly see whot we was doing\nwher we set our editerial, and begun\nat the bottom and set it ali up back\nend to, as you might say. As we\nbroke our specs when we fell we\ncouldn't see this until we went to\npress and it was too late for us to change\nii\n\n\n\n\n\n\n1\n\n\n\nand git the Bugle out this week. As for\nBill he ort to be ashaimed of hisself for\ngitting drunk when he has a respectful\nfeller townsman with him and editorially\nspeakin we will never again go to the Co,\nseat with a man that drinks strong licker\n\u2014net by a jugful.\n\n\nPersonals\nSime Peters had eccashion to look inte\none of his bee hives the other day, and\nto his turrible disgust he found that al}\nhis bees was froze dead. Sime sed he\ndidn\u2019t dream it was sich a cold winter we\nhad went through.\n\nHen Weathersby, prop. of our general\nstore, has receeved a stock of ladies\u2019\nstockings wich he ordered for last fall\nand sold two pr. right off toc Phoebe Hil\nderbrand who brought them back the next\nday. Phoebe seq they looked long enuff,\nbut when she put them on it made them\ntoo short for her.\nMiss Jane McCrackin is havin a new\ndress cut out by her mother. Uniess it\nfits Jane better than the last one her\nmother made for her. wa feel gorry for\nJane, for that last dress caused a good\neal of talk around town.\nMrs. Cy Hoskins went to the Co. seat\nlast week and hought a barl of flour and\na big box ef groceries and the next day\nCy went into Hen Weathersby's and paid\nHen the bal, of whot he owed him. Cy\nsed he saved that much on his goods by\ngettin them in a lump. Hen says he is\nglad to get his money, but that aint no\nway to paternise home trade.\nMrs. Martha Tucker is now able to get\nout and talk with the -nabers after being\nhoused in al! winter with a bunyan en\nher right foot. She cut a hole in h\u00e9r\nshoe so her toe joint could stick out and\nnow enjoys every steps she takes.\nThe Bingville church needs\nawful bad. The Deacons talked some of\npainting it last fall, but somehow or oth\ner they didn\u2019t get around to it.\npainting\nIsrael Goodwin, more familiar knowd\nas \u201cIs\u201d caught his hand in a glass jar\nBt he stirs Saitiriny uaht walle Sve\n9 son out a twisted peppermint stick and\nThere is menny indicashions wich in\nto smash same before hie got it out.\nAs we go to press Snake Crick, wich\npasses through our midst is on its regu\niar spring rampage and is rising at the\nrate of two inches a hour. It commenced\nlast Wednesday to swell up follewing the\nthaw wich set in a few davs ago meltin\nthe snow {n the mountings and has grad\nually increased in volume until the erick\nis running over in some places, If them\nof you don\u2019t get the Bugle next week or\nthe week after you will know that our\nprinting office is warshed offen tlie map\nand that like as not we have got wet to\nthe skin sailing around on a barn door\nand died of tiephoyd fever or some\nthink similar.\n\n\n\n\ntt\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nErbout a hour ago Abe Whittacre called\nat the Bugle offise to tell us that Hame\nWilson who lives right on the crick\nmoved out this merning owing to the\nfackt that his wife objeckted to wadin\naround in water two ft. deep in order\nto do her house work and dust off the\nfurniture. Hame intended to move out\nennyhow erbout May Ist, but being as\nthe watter has riz so rapidly he moeved\nsooner. Hame's household goods and per\nsonnel chattels, as you might say, is now\non top of Teck\u2019's Hill where Hame thinks\nthey will be safe for a few days at\nleast,\n\n\n\n\n\nRanse Smiley, whe also lives close to\nthe crick is now living in the seckoned\nstery of his house. Ranse has a boat\nand says he Is going to stick to his\nhouse as long as there is enny of it in|\neight above wat\u2018er. All his hens and a\npig is in one room up stairs and Ranse\ngot enuff eggs for breakfast this morn\ning to pay for the trouble of carting them\nup there,\nSome eof our most respectful eitizens\nhave packed up their goods and are\nreddy to move if the watter comes up\nmuch higher.\nLATER-Cy Hosking was jest in and\nhe says he thinks the flood is subsiding,\nbut as a precaushionary move he has\nordered the Snake Rend saw mill to\nstart up full ferce to use up 2s much\nsurplus watter as possible, and thinks\nBingville will exscape with the loss of\nonly one hen house and severa. I\nchickhen eoops. i\n\n\nLank Spiled It\nMrs, Jerushy Perkins left a mountain\nof coffee jelly and cream on our desk\nlast week and receeved our thanks. We\nwas purty bizzy at the time and didn't\nthink ennythink more erbout it until\nLank Jones ast us whot in tarnashion\nhe had sot on. We jooked up, and to our\nhorror and disgust there was our jelly\nand cream plastered all over the seat of\nhis pants with the sawser bruk in erbout\n17 pieces and still clinging to him. We\ninvited Lank to clear aut befers we lest\ncur temper and the last we see of him he\nwas serapin hisself on the palings of Cy\nHoskins\u2019 fence.\ni\n\n\n\nSchool Closed Thursday\nThe short wood in the Bingville school\nhouse shed Is being used by seme low\ndown theef that's too blamed lazy te\ntake the long sticks and saw them, and\nJed Peters, our inteliijent school teacher,\nhad to close school last Thursday on that\nacst. Jed and some of the schollars then\nsawed enuff to last the bal. of the week\nand piled it up in the school reem under\nlock and key. Hank Dewberry heerd er\nbout it down to the store and tola the\ngelectmen that he had erbout shords\nof wood that he had sawed up in his\nspare time, this winter, that he would\nsell cheep, and the seleetmen bought\nthree cords offen him se that the school\ncan keep open until vacasrion,\n\n\n\ni\n3\n\n\nMiss Phoebe Hilderbrand, our talented\ndr\u00e9ssmaker, has returned from a 2 days\u2019\nvisit to the County seat with a large\nsupply of patterns she bought at a clos\nIng out sale at a little store that had\nbeen in business forty yeers. Ennyone\nwhot wants a new Easter basque or pol\nonaise made must call at once, as she\nexpeckts to be turrible bizzy.\n\n\n\n\n\nHeek Barclay has jest got rid of a boil\non his neck and now has anuther one\ncomin. This is the fourth boil Heck has\nhad since the first of the month. He says\nit is gettin to be turrible monotonous\nwith him.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nDave White, our popular undertaker,\nhas told the boys of the Ringville Horn\nBand that they could use his shop to\nprackiise in until business picks up this\nspring.\ni\ni\nBud in Trouble Asain\nBud Hinckley, who aint quite right in\nhis head, while plaving hide and look\ntother day, got into a flour barl and\ncouldn't get out until his mother chopped\nthe hoops offen it. Bud he was awful\nskeard at first but when he got out he\njest erbout laffed hisself to deth until\nMrs. Hinckley got mad and whaled him\nfor makin sich a f#0l of hisself.\n\n\n\nCountry Correspondence\nBili Hendrick's wife of Zion Crossroads\nwho has been vissitin Mrs. Ransom Tay\nlor, terminated her visit ruther sudden\nvesterday morning and has returned home\nfor an indefinite stay.\n\nJeremy Hooker druv td the Co. seat\nlast week with a load of shook. He done\nseveral errunds for the nabers and come\nhome with a purty good a\nMiss Lucinda Watkins had the earache\nthe other day erbout 4 a. m., but is much\nbetter as we write this.\nEben Williams who is workin over at\nSnake Bend spent Sunday at home.\nMiss Rose Snyder, the bell of Flinch\nville, attended a theatre show at the Co.\nseat last week, and is now thinking some\nof going on the stage to sing and dance\nher way to fame and forchunme. If she\ndoes, she will leave one sad heart be\nhind, won't she, Hiram?\nYour correspondent expeekts to get a\nnew subscriber next week and has almost\nclosed the dicker, The party wants sam\nple copies for three mos, and we are hold.\ning out fer two. LIBERTY,\n\nELDERBERRY GAD\n\nAdam Cutler vissited Hardscrabble last\nweek and bought a haff bushel of clams.\n\nHans Derflinger while dressing a steer\nhad the knife to slip and cut two fingers.\nHans was awful surprised but took it\ngeod natured being as the fingers was on\na nuther feller's hand whe was helpin\nhim.\nRebecca Sprigging has had to let out\nthe seams fn her Sunday dress she's git\ntin that stout. Nine years makes quite\na diff\u00e9rents in a person's stoutness or\nthinness, as you might say.\nSeth Dobbins, who has shaved hisseif\nall winter and put 3 cts, in 2 china apple\nbank each time, broke the bank tother\nday and found $1.13. Seth says he must\nof cheated hisself outen 2 cts. some time\nor other.\nSnide Emmons had a flare-up with Mii\nlv Hobbs Wednesday night on acct, of\nHank Skinner askin her to go to a party\nwith him. Snide didn\u2019t find it out until\nthe next night after she went.\nj\nLige Simmons druv to tha Co. seat last\npier Lo gg of whot he calis\nJestap pam. He looks like a bottle bug\nt\nAndrew White while makin some het\nginger tea for his eold vesterday had the\nkettle to slip en him and spii] some boil\ning watter on his feet. Only for his cow\nhides he might have been burned to deth.\n8IC BEMPER TRYANN.\nLocals\nHBOYLITON DUPUMER. '08.\nFLINCHVILLFE\nA\n2A Ok\nZia\nANNUAL\nSPRING\nCLEARANCE\nSALE\n\nEvery spring I held a big sale of goods which\nHave Had in Stock\nfor Five or Ten\nYears Back\nthan\nIn Small Messes\nand charging them up\ndo by deling goods out\nJed Peters took a inventors fer me this winter\nend went over my stock of goods and ended up\nin my show case and\nsays he was syr\nprised to see whot\na nise line of goods\n\u201cihad stored Way\nFur Caps\nFur Coats\nMitts, Boots\nHeavy Wool\nUnderware\nThey\nsnd o Nile goods 8 I Ml cheep in order\n5 git shet and the\nMots Which st Several\nMeals Offfen Them\nSale Begins Next Monday\nand Will Last all the\nWeek or Longer\nYOURS FOR BARGAINS\nWEATHERSBY\nProp. Bingville Gen. Store.\nI\nFOR SAIL\nI have decided to quit repairing\nFri\nfam a es to sell of all my tools and\ngead will\nfor wich I will take 75 cents. There is no\nnioney in the umbrella fixing bisness in Bing\nHoge and\n1 donk think 75 ets, is too much for\nepening In this line\nSee about this offer before it is grabd ap.\nIEE DOOLITTLR,\nBingrills, Umbrella Repairer.","height":"39864","width":"27212"}}
